NAME
  bang - Bash4 Framework for easy script creation

SYNOPSIS
  bang test [test_file1 test_file2 test_dir1 test_dir2 ...]

DESCRIPTION
  For each file given and files in the directories given
  runs the test functions and print their output.

  If no file or directory is passed to the `test` task,
  it runs all files under `test/` directory.

EXAMPLES
  bang test test/my_test.sh
  bang test test/my_test.sh test/modules
  bang test test/modules/*sh

SEE ALSO
  bang(1) bang-new(1) bang-run(1)

AUTHOR
